3. 
<taxonomicName authority="Tan et al., 2017" authorityName="Tan et al." authorityYear="2017" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Alloteratura" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Alloteratura (Alloteratura) belalongensis" order="Orthoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="belalongensis" subGenus="Alloteratura">Alloteratura (Alloteratura) belalongensis Tan et al., 2017</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="119" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="119">Remarks.-</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="119">
This is one of the four new species of 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="119" rank="tribe" tribe="Meconematini">Meconematini</taxonomicName>
katydids collected and described from Kuala Belalong. This new species is very similar to 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. (A.) karnyi" pageId="0" pageNumber="119" rank="species" species="karnyi" subGenus="A.">A. (A.) karnyi</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Kästner">Kaestner</normalizedToken>
, 1932 from northern Sumatra (
<bibRefCitation author="Kaestner, A" journalOrPublisher="Stettiner Entomologische Zeitung" pageId="1" pageNumber="120" pagination="163 - 182" title="Die Meconeminae des Stettiner Museums." volume="93" year="1932">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Kästner">Kaestner</normalizedToken>
1932
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Gorochov, AV" journalOrPublisher="Zoosystematica Rossica" pageId="0" pageNumber="119" pagination="101 - 131" title="New and little known Meconematinae of the tribes Meconematini and Phlugidini (Orthoptera: Tettigoniidae)." volume="7" year="1998 a">Gorochov 1998a</bibRefCitation>
) and Thailand (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Saenger, K" journalOrPublisher="Senckenbergiana Biologica" pageId="1" pageNumber="120" pagination="141 - 147" title="Notes on the Meconematinae fauna (Ensifera, Tettigoniidae) of Thailand." volume="80" year="2000">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Sänger">Saenger</normalizedToken>
and Helfert 2000
</bibRefCitation>
) but could belong to several different subspecies of the same species owing to the similarities in morphology (
<bibRefCitation author="Tan, MK" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="1" pageNumber="120" pagination="390 - 402" title="New taxa and notes of katydids from the tribe Meconematini (Orthoptera: Meconematinae) from Brunei Darussalam." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4337.3.4" volume="4337" year="2017 d">Tan et al. 2017d</bibRefCitation>
). We need more material around Southeast Asia and study of their population genetics to confirm species limits. Refer to 
<bibRefCitation author="Tan, MK" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="1" pageNumber="120" pagination="390 - 402" title="New taxa and notes of katydids from the tribe Meconematini (Orthoptera: Meconematinae) from Brunei Darussalam." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4337.3.4" volume="4337" year="2017 d">Tan et al. (2017d)</bibRefCitation>
for the new species description.
</paragraph>
